+# ExecHealth Observability Runbook (v1)
+
+Files:
+- `orderflow_services/prometheus_alerts_exec_health_observability_v1.yml`
+- `orderflow_services/grafana/exec_health_observability_v1.json`
+
+## What is the source of truth
+
+Policy/threshold semantics come from:
+- `services/orderflow/exec_health_rollups.py`
+
+Metrics are emitted only from the already-evaluated SoT path via:
+- `services/orderflow/exec_health_observability.py`
+
+This means dashboards/alerts observe the same `rollups + decision` that were used by:
+- `SignalPipeline`
+- `EntryPolicyService`
+- `EdgeCostGate`
+
+## Fast triage
+
+Check effective policy mode and thresholds:
+- `exec_health_policy_mode`
+- `exec_health_policy_threshold_bps`
+
+Check whether rollups are actually present:
+- `exec_health_rollup_present`
+- `exec_health_rollup_value_bps`
+- `exec_health_rollup_worst_delta_sec`
+
+Check if fail-open is masking read issues:
+- `increase(exec_health_reader_errors_total[5m])`
+
+Check path outcomes:
+- `increase(exec_health_decision_total[15m])`
+- `increase(exec_health_flag_total[15m])`
+
+## Typical failure modes
+
+1. `exec_health_reader_errors_total` increases
+   - Redis unavailable / wrong DB / wrong key namespace
+   - TCA writer lagging or absent
+   - mixed deployment with stale key contracts
+
+2. `exec_health_rollup_present == 0` while `exec_health_last_event_ts_ms` is fresh
+   - live traffic exists, but no TCA rollups are matching fallback keys
+   - check `venue/session/tf/kind/side` normalization
+
+3. Veto storm
+   - thresholds too tight for current regime
+   - stale/incorrect TCA rollups
+   - recent microstructure regime shift
